message.content: The likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are "cs.IR", "cs.CL", "cs.AI", "cs.LG", and "cs.CY". The paper deals with the task of FAQ retrieval, which involves information retrieval and natural language processing techniques. The use of BERT for relevance calculation suggests a focus on language modeling and deep learning, which are common in the sub-categories of "cs.CL", "cs.AI", and "cs.LG". The use of unsupervised information retrieval also suggests a focus on information retrieval, which is common in the sub-category of "cs.IR". Finally, the use of a dataset in a specific domain (Japanese administrative municipality) suggests a focus on domain-specific applications, which is common in the sub-category of "cs.CY" (computational and data-driven approaches to social sciences).
